      "message": "Have you verified that this works?  I suspect that the recipe engine will error out on \"/tmp\" (it doesn\u0027t want you to write anything permanent on the machine).  There are ways to hack around it (see https://skia.googlesource.com/skia/+/master/infra/bots/recipes/ct_skps.py#42) but the better approach would probably be to use a named cache.  You\u0027d specify it in gen_tasks.go, similar to https://skia.googlesource.com/skia/+/master/infra/bots/gen_tasks.go#132 and then use it like self.m.vars.cache_dir.join(\u0027wasm\u0027).",
